BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-outer-ear-2026-2@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261030
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261031
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: Outer Ear Special Programme (Round 2026/2)
DESCRIPTION:Outer Ear is Musikfonds' dedicated special programme for partic
 ipatory projects in experimental music\, and the strand that most cleanly 
 matches an experimental and sound-art public-programme brief rather than c
 oncert-series funding. It emphasises the creative process and audience par
 ticipation over finished works\, explicitly targeting audiences for experi
 mental music\, which makes it suitable for workshop-plus-presentation form
 ats\, listening programmes and process-led sound art events. Application w
 indows run twice yearly: 1 to 30 April 2026 (closed) and 1 to 30 October 2
 026\, the next live deadline. THE FIRST OUTER EAR ROUND WAS HIGHLY COMPETI
 TIVE\, with 14 projects approved at an 8.6 percent success rate\, so treat
  it as a long shot. As with all Musikfonds strands\, the applicant must be
  based in Germany\, projects abroad are ineligible\, and double-funding wi
 th BKM or with projects run by permanently institutionally supported bodie
 s is excluded. Note that Musikfonds' Small and Large Project Funding stran
 ds are listed separately in the Grant Desk\; Outer Ear is a distinct progr
 amme with its own window.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germ
 any. Projects taking place abroad are excluded.\nAward: FLAG\, UNVERIFIED:
  per-project amounts are not published on the programme overview page and 
 must be confirmed via the application portal at musikfonds-antrag.de. No a
 pplication fee indicated.\nDuration: Project-based.\n\nMore: https://www.m
 usikfonds.de/foerderprogramme/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme/?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Projects taking place abroad are excluded.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:norma-fonds-projectbijdrage-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261030
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261031
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stichting NORMA: NORMA Fonds Project Grant (round 4\, 202
 6)
DESCRIPTION:The NORMA Fonds redistributes copyright remuneration collected 
 by Stichting NORMA into cultural\, social and professional projects involv
 ing performing artists\, and is one of the few Dutch schemes with four int
 akes a year and a genuinely short cycle. Both arts-sector organisations an
 d individual arts professionals may apply\, though the applicant needs a b
 ank account and legal footing and cannot be a BIS-funded institution. The 
 project must centre on performing artists in the copyright sense\, meaning
  people who perform a copyright-protected work: musicians\, dancers\, acto
 rs\, voice actors. This fits live experimental music\, sound performance a
 nd performative media-art work\, but not object-based exhibitions or non-p
 erformative installation programmes. The maximum grant is EUR 10\,000\, th
 e total project budget must stay under EUR 150\,000\, the applicant's annu
 al budget under EUR 500\,000\, and at least a quarter of the project budge
 t must be earned from audience income\, so this is a top-up rather than a 
 primary funding source. Budgets must honour NORMA's 2026 performer wage no
 rms. Applications are submitted online during a one-month window each quar
 ter\; the next round runs 1 to 30 October 2026\, closing at 23:59. TIMING 
 RULE: decisions arrive no later than eight weeks after the deadline\, and 
 the premiere date must fall at least eight weeks after the application dea
 dline. Organisations that already received a NORMA Fonds grant in 2024 or 
 2025 are excluded\, and supporting staff may not exceed 2 FTE.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Stichting NORMA (collecting society for performing artists)\nLocatio
 n: Netherlands-based arts-sector activity. No city or region restriction s
 tated.\nAward: Maximum EUR 10\,000 per project. Total project budget may n
 ot exceed EUR 150\,000 and the applicant organisation's annual budget may 
 not exceed EUR 500\,000. At least 25 percent of the project budget must co
 me from audience or box-office revenue. Performer fees must meet the 2026 
 wage norms of EUR 139 per rehearsal and EUR 340 per performance. No applic
 ation fee.\nDuration: Single project\, typically a production or concert s
 eries. Final report due within six months of completion.\n\nMore: https://
 www.stichtingnorma.nl/norma-fonds/aanvragen/?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stichtingnorma.nl/norma-fonds/aanvragen/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands-based arts-sector activity. No city or region restrict
 ion stated.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ernst-von-siemens-musikstiftung-project-funding-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Ernst von Siemens Musikstiftung: Project Funding (October
  2026 round)
DESCRIPTION:One of the largest private funders of contemporary and new musi
 c in Europe\, and it funds the organising side of the field rather than in
 dividual artists\, which makes it directly usable by festivals. Eligible a
 ctivity includes festivals\, world premieres and revivals\, composition co
 mmissions\, events\, academies and workshops\, education projects\, sympos
 ia and musicological publications. Experimental and contemporary sound pro
 gramming is the core remit\; this is not a classical-repertoire fund. Ther
 e are two annual deadlines: 1 October at 14:00 CEST for projects starting 
 the following year with decisions by year-end\, and 1 March for projects s
 tarting in July or later with decisions by end of June. Grant sizes are no
 t published\, and the Foundation aims funding at artistic rather than over
 head costs. Only the organising institution may apply and only legal entit
 ies qualify: cultural institutions\, orchestra managers\, festival organis
 ers and ensembles. Self-applications and applications from individuals are
  explicitly refused. VOLUME LIMITS are strict and worth planning around: e
 ach institution may submit one application per deadline\, may be supported
  for only one project per year\, and may be supported for a maximum of thr
 ee projects across three consecutive years.\n\nOrganisation: Ernst von Sie
 mens Musikstiftung\nLocation: International\, no stated country restrictio
 n on the organising institution\, though the Foundation is Swiss and Germa
 n in orientation and administration.\nAward: No published minimum or maxim
 um. Primarily covers artistic costs\, not overheads. The Foundation explic
 itly will not fully fund a project\, and requires at least one other insti
 tution to participate financially at a level similar to the amount request
 ed\, functioning as a de facto 1:1 match. No application fee.\nDuration: P
 roject-based. The October deadline covers projects beginning the following
  calendar year.\n\nMore: https://evs-musikstiftung.ch/en/project-funding/a
 pplication/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://evs-musikstiftung.ch/en/project-funding/application/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:International\, no stated country restriction on the organising in
 stitution\, though the Foundation is Swiss and German in orientation and a
 dministration.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlinale-talents-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlinale Talents 2027 (Berlin International Film Festiva
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Berlinale Talents is the Berlin International Film Festival's t
 alent-development program: a week of workshops\, the Talents Lab and the T
 alent Project Market during the February 2027 Berlinale\, plus access to t
 he festival's industry network. ELIGIBILITY: international working film pr
 ofessionals with at least 1 feature\, 2 shorts\, or a widely screened or s
 treamed series\, across 15+ disciplines including directing\, sound design
 \, editing\, production\, cinematography and screenwriting. Participation 
 itself is free\; there is a EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early b
 ird before 19 August 2026) and travel and accommodation are not covered. D
 eadline 2 September 2026\, 12:00 CEST. Apply via the Berlinale Talents por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Berlinale / Berlin International Film Festival\nLoca
 tion: Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open inter
 nationally.\nAward: Free participation in the week-long professional progr
 am (Summit workshops\, Talents Lab\, Talent Project Market\, industry netw
 orking). NO stipend\; travel and accommodation are self-covered (national 
 film institutes often fund this\; Netherlands-based filmmakers can approac
 h the Netherlands Film Fund). EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early
  bird before 19 August 2026).\nDuration: One week during the Berlinale\, F
 ebruary 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open int
 ernationally.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlin-senate-arbeitsstipendium-bildende-kunst-2027@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlin Senate: Arbeitsstipendium Bildende Kunst 2027 (Ber
 lin residents only)
DESCRIPTION:The Berlin Senate's work stipends for visual artists fund 8 or 
 12 months of artistic work during 2027 at EUR 2\,000 per month. The progra
 m explicitly covers digital art and media art\, sound art\, artistic film 
 and video (shown in a visual-arts exhibition context) and installation\, a
 longside classical visual-arts disciplines. ELIGIBILITY: professional visu
 al artists who live\, work and are registered in Berlin\; not open to appl
 icants based elsewhere. The application window runs 6 July to 2 September 
 2026\, 11:00 CEST\, via the Senate's online portal.\n\nOrganisation: Berli
 n Senate Department for Culture and Social Cohesion\nLocation: Berlin\, Ge
 rmany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, work and be officiall
 y registered in Berlin.\nAward: EUR 16\,000 (8 months) or EUR 24\,000 (12 
 months)\, paid as EUR 2\,000 per month. No application fee.\nDuration: 8 o
 r 12 months during 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/fundi
 ng/funding-programmes/visual-arts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/funding/funding-programmes/visual-a
 rts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium
 =referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, wo
 rk and be officially registered in Berlin.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cmc-dmarc-sonic-arts-residency-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260805
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260806
SUMMARY:Deadline: CMC/DMARC Sonic Arts Residency 2026/2027
DESCRIPTION:The Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC) and CMC Irel
 and announce the second year of the Sonic Arts Residency Programme at the 
 University of Limerick Electronic Music Studio for 2026/27. The residency 
 offers Irish and international composers and sound artists an opportunity 
 to develop their creative practice and experiment using UL's facilities. F
 ACILITIES: the Electronic Music Studio (EMS) featuring both digital and an
 alogue workflows\, including a bespoke Buchla 200e\; a 32-channel immersiv
 e sound lab (SpADE)\; a makerspace supporting electronics and fabrication\
 ; and a range of well-equipped recording studios with a wide selection of 
 microphones and production hardware and software. DMARC is based in the Co
 mputer Science and Information Systems Department at UL and has a long his
 tory supporting digital arts\, electronic music\, and computer-aided compo
 sition (hosting the 2022 International Computer Music Conference and 2020 
 International Conference on Live Coding\, the Diffusion Prize with RTE Lyr
 ic FM\, and partnering with Light Moves Festival). PROGRAMME: each residen
 cy lasts 10 working days within one of two windows\, September-December 20
 26 or January-March 2027. Support includes a EUR 1\,000 honorarium from CM
 C\, a travel bursary up to EUR 350\, and an accommodation bursary up to EU
 R 1\,400 (ten nights)\, with DMARC helping identify accommodation. There i
 s an outreach/presentation element: a one-hour talk/performance for the DM
 ARC community of students and researchers\, and required documentation of 
 the process (photo\, video\, recordings\, and/or written reflections) that
  may be published by CMC on social media\; artists may also be invited to 
 contribute to CMC's amplify podcast series or online features at cmc.ie/fe
 atures. The programme runs 2025-27 with support for six artists (4 Irish\,
  2 international). ASSESSMENT: candidates apply via an online form submitt
 ing a CV\, work samples\, an outline of the residency project (including t
 echnical requirements)\, how they propose to engage with the facilities\, 
 and how the residency would benefit their practice. Criteria: artistic qua
 lity of the proposal including development of work using either the SpADE 
 system or Buchla 200e\; how the opportunity supports the candidate's curre
 nt career stage and artistic goals\; demonstrated technical capacity to en
 gage with the facilities\; and balanced representation of genres\, gender\
 , and geographical regions. TO APPLY: complete the online application form
  linked from the opportunity page. Closing date: 11am (IST)\, 5 August 202
 6\; late applications will not be accepted. Questions: jurgen.simpson@ul.i
 e or kfennell@cmc.ie. Applications are jointly assessed by DMARC and the C
 ontemporary Music Centre.\n\nOrganisation: Contemporary Music Centre (CMC)
  & Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC)\, University of Limerick
 \nLocation: University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).\nAwar
 d: EUR 1\,000 honorarium (from CMC)\, plus a travel bursary up to EUR 350 
 and an accommodation bursary up to EUR 1\,400 (ten nights). No application
  fee.\nDuration: 10 working days\, scheduled within one of two windows: Se
 ptember-December 2026 or January-March 2027. Additional time may be reques
 ted where it does not incur extra cost.\n\nMore: http://cmc.ie/opportuniti
 es/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-20262027?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:http://cmc.ie/opportunities/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-202
 62027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-toyful-music-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Atheras: Nicosia Ludic Lab for Composers\, Toyful Music F
 estival 2026
DESCRIPTION:Atheras Peoples and Cultures invites composers and performer-re
 searchers to apply for the Nicosia Ludic Lab\, a 31-day international resi
 dency dedicated to exploring 'play' as a compositional and performative me
 thodology in contemporary music. Building on the artistic vision of the To
 yful Music Festival\, the residency creates a focused environment where ex
 perimentation\, precision\, and imagination coexist\, redefining how music
  is conceived\, structured\, and performed. The residency runs in Nicosia\
 , Cyprus\, from 23 October to 22 November 2026\, and participants develop 
 new ensemble works that directly shape the artistic programme of the Toyfu
 l Music Festival 2026. ELIGIBILITY: applications are open to individual ar
 tists (proposals from duets or collectives will not be considered) based i
 n a Creative Europe country\, who must demonstrate a strong interest in ex
 perimental\, ensemble-based practices. SELECTED RESIDENTS RECEIVE: full fi
 nancial support (travel\, accommodation\, daily allowance)\; shared accomm
 odation in central Nicosia\; continuous access to a professional ensemble\
 ; mentorship sessions and individual meetings with ensemble members\; coac
 hing sessions with composer and conductor Andys Skordis\; artistic and pro
 fessional guidance from the Atheras team\; rehearsal space and full produc
 tion support for Phase 3\; and video and audio recording of the final live
  concert for documentation and international visibility. Deadline: 15 July
  2026.\n\nOrganisation: Atheras Peoples and Cultures\nLocation: Nicosia\, 
 Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative Europe country\nAw
 ard: Full financial support: travel\, shared accommodation in central Nico
 sia\, and daily allowance. Rehearsal space and full production support pro
 vided\; final live concert recorded (video and audio) for documentation an
 d international visibility.\nDuration: 31-day residency\, 23 October to 22
  November 2026\n\nMore: https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic
 -lab-composers-new-works-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-composers-new-wo
 rks-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nicosia\, Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative 
 Europe country
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vfa-sonic-connections-open-call-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sonic Connections Open Call 2027 (Villa Filanda Antonini)
DESCRIPTION:Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA) launches its Spring Open Call to s
 elect up to 4 artists and professionals for a one-month residency in March
  2027 on the theme 'Sonic Connections'\, focused on experimental music\, s
 ound art\, and performances. Hosted at Villa Filanda Antonini\, a former s
 ilk mill in Villorba\, Italy\, the project brings together four internatio
 nal artists and professionals to examine the relationship between architec
 ture\, landscape\, and collective sonic experience. ADDRESSED TO: artists\
 , performers\, curators\, designers\, and professionals not currently resi
 ding in Italy. GRANT & BENEFITS: a fully funded residency covering mentori
 ng\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily salary\
 , plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend. WHEN: 1-31 March 2027. HOW TO APPLY
 : complete the application form and attach a CV\, portfolio\, project prop
 osal\, and letter of reference. The VFA residency program has been selecte
 d under conditions by Culture Moves Europe\, a project funded by the Europ
 ean Union and implemented by the Goethe-Institut. Deadline: 19 July 2026\,
  23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA)\nLocation: Vill
 orba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and professionals 
 NOT currently residing in Italy.\nAward: Fully funded residency covering m
 entoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily s
 alary\, plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend.\nDuration: One-month residenc
 y\, 1-31 March 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections
 -open-call-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections-open-call-2027/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Villorba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and pr
 ofessionals NOT currently residing in Italy.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-stip-6-ai-scholarship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: STIP-6 AI Scholarship Programme 2027 (Germany
 )
DESCRIPTION:STIP-6 is a Musikfonds scholarship programme supporting profess
 ional musicians who work on AI-based composition and who reflect criticall
 y and societally on the role of artificial intelligence in music. Ten scho
 larships of EUR 30\,000 each are awarded for the 2027 working year. Open t
 o Germany-based professional freelance musicians across genres\; no comput
 er-science or technical background is required. Deadline 30 June 2026\, 18
 :00 CET. Details and application via the Musikfonds funding programmes pag
 e (apply at musikfonds-antrag.de). NOTE: this entry was sourced from resea
 rch and the funder's pages may update\; confirm current figures and deadli
 ne before applying.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germany. O
 pen to Germany-based professional freelance musicians\; no computer-scienc
 e background required.\nAward: EUR 30\,000 lump sum per scholarship\, paid
  in twelve monthly installments across January to December 2027. Ten schol
 arships available. No application fee.\nDuration: Twelve months (January t
 o December 2027).\n\nMore: https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Open to Germany-based professional freelance musicians\; 
 no computer-science background required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-small-project-funding-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: Small Project Funding (New and Experimental M
 usic) 2026 (Germany)
DESCRIPTION:Musikfonds Small Project Funding supports new\, experimental an
 d contemporary music projects with grants of up to EUR 3\,000\, prioritisi
 ng projects in rural and structurally weaker regions of Germany. A minimum
  10 percent co-financing is required and the artist fee must be at least E
 UR 350 per concert. Applicants and projects must be based in Germany. Appl
 ication windows close 31 August 2026 and 30 November 2026. NOTE: research-
 sourced\; confirm current figures and window dates on the Musikfonds site 
 before applying.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germany. Appl
 icants and projects based in Germany\; priority to rural and structurally 
 weaker regions.\nAward: Up to EUR 3\,000 per project (minimum 10 percent c
 o-financing\; artist fee at least EUR 350 per concert). No application fee
 .\nDuration: Project-based.\n\nMore: https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprog
 ramme?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Applicants and projects based in Germany\; priority to ru
 ral and structurally weaker regions.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-large-project-funding-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260930
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261001
SUMMARY:Deadline: Musikfonds: Large Project Funding (New and Experimental M
 usic) 2026 (Germany)
DESCRIPTION:Musikfonds Large Project Funding supports new\, experimental an
 d contemporary music projects with grants of up to EUR 50\,000. A minimum 
 10 percent co-financing is required and the artist fee must be at least EU
 R 300 per concert. Applicants and projects must be based in Germany\; pure
  audio or video productions\, university projects and amateur-only project
 s are excluded. The application window runs 1 to 30 September 2026. NOTE: 
 research-sourced\; confirm current figures and window dates on the Musikfo
 nds site before applying.\n\nOrganisation: musikfonds e.V.\nLocation: Germ
 any. Applicants and projects based in Germany\; excludes pure audio/video 
 productions\, university and amateur-only projects.\nAward: Up to EUR 50\,
 000 per project (minimum 10 percent co-financing\; artist fee at least EUR
  300 per concert). No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based.\n\nMore: 
 https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.musikfonds.de/foerderprogramme?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. Applicants and projects based in Germany\; excludes pure 
 audio/video productions\, university and amateur-only projects.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:music-worx-incubator-hamburg-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Deadline: Music WorX: Music-Tech Incubator 2026 (Hamburg)
DESCRIPTION:Music WorX is the music-technology incubator run by Hamburg Kre
 ativ Gesellschaft for early-stage teams building products at the intersect
 ion of music and technology (creation tools\, interactive media\, streamin
 g and monetisation\, AI for music\, instruments and audio gear). Selected 
 teams receive a EUR 3\,200 development budget for support services plus a 
 EUR 1\,500 per month living allowance over the 3-month programme\, mentori
 ng from a European music-tech network\, and the chance to win a EUR 1\,000
  audience prize and a EUR 2\,500 jury prize at demo day. The incubator tak
 es no equity. Open to European founders and founding teams (teams of at le
 ast two recommended\, solo founders welcome)\; no formal company formation
  is required to apply. The programme runs roughly September to December 20
 26. Application deadline: 17 June 2026. Apply via the Airtable form linked
  from the official programme page.\n\nOrganisation: Hamburg Kreativ Gesell
 schaft (Kreativ Gesellschaft)\nLocation: Hamburg\, Germany. Open to Europe
 an founders and founding teams\; Hamburg-anchored program with a European 
 mentor network.\nAward: EUR 3\,200 development budget per team plus a EUR 
 1\,500 per month living allowance across the 3-month programme. End-of-pro
 gramme prizes: EUR 1\,000 audience award and EUR 2\,500 jury award. No equ
 ity is taken. No application fee.\nDuration: 3-month programme\, roughly e
 arly September to early December 2026.\n\nMore: https://kreativgesellschaf
 t.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/music-worx/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kreativgesellschaft.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/m
 usic-worx/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hamburg\, Germany. Open to European founders and founding teams\; 
 Hamburg-anchored program with a European mentor network.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mota-production-residency-ljubljana-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:Deadline: MoTA Museum of Transitory Art: Production Residency 2027 
 (Ljubljana)
DESCRIPTION:MoTA (Museum of Transitory Art) in Ljubljana runs an annual ope
 n call for production residencies for media\, sound and visual artists\, c
 urators and researchers. Production residencies offer full support includi
 ng accommodation\, technical support\, production costs and an artist fee\
 ; the exact artist-fee amount is not published on the official or aggregat
 or pages\, so applicants should confirm the figure directly by email. Resi
 dencies run up to one month. Open internationally: artists of all national
 ities and at all professional levels are encouraged to apply\, as individu
 als or collectives. No application fee. The annual deadline is 15 Septembe
 r (for residencies the following year). Apply by email to mota.artists@gma
 il.com with the subject line Application for production residency. Note: t
 he official motamuseum.com SSL certificate is currently expired\, which ma
 y briefly affect link reliability.\n\nOrganisation: MoTA - Museum of Trans
 itory Art\nLocation: Ljubljana\, Slovenia. Open internationally to artists
  of all nationalities and professional levels.\nAward: Full support includ
 ing accommodation\, technical support\, production costs and an artist fee
 . The exact EUR artist-fee amount is not published\; confirm by email. No 
 application fee.\nDuration: Production residency of up to one month.\n\nMo
 re: http://motamuseum.com/RESIDENCY/open-call?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:http://motamuseum.com/RESIDENCY/open-call?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Ljubljana\, Slovenia. Open internationally to artists of all natio
 nalities and professional levels.
