DESCRIPTION:CTM Festival's Radio Lab commissions new radio-based sound work
 s around the CTM 2027 theme In Listening\, premiered at the festival in Be
 rlin and broadcast on Deutschlandfunk Kultur. The previous cycle's commiss
 ion was EUR 5\,000 plus travel and lodging\; the 2027 fee is not restated 
 on the call page. Open worldwide. The same open-calls page also lists the 
 Resynthesising the Traditional 2027 artistic lab (same 6 September 2026 de
 adline) and Research Networking Day 2027 (deadline 25 October 2026). Radio
  Lab deadline 6 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: CTM Festival with Deutsch
 landfunk Kultur\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany. Premiered at CTM 2027 and bro
 adcast on Deutschlandfunk Kultur\, with onward broadcast via ORF Oe1 and m
 usikprotokoll. No nationality restrictions are stated\; the form asks for 
 citizenship but excludes no nationality.\nAward: Two selected works are ea
 ch supported by a fee of EUR 6\,000. CTM covers travel to Berlin and lodgi
 ng during the production and festival periods\, and technical and staging 
 costs for the CTM presentation are covered separately by arrangement. Rese
 arch\, creation and collaborator costs are the artist's own. No applicatio
 n fee.\nDuration: Work premiered at CTM Festival\, 22-31 January 2027.\n\n
 More: https://www.ctm-festival.de/festival-2027/open-calls/in-listening-20
 27?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
